MTF<br>
I've never forgotten how you told me you and SW first met.<br>
If I remember correctly this is how it happened.<br><br>
Sw went skydiving for the first time. After listening to the instructor<br>
for what seems like days, he was ready to go. <br><br>
Excited, he jumped out of the airplane. After a bit, he pulls the ripcord. Nothing happened. <br><br>
He tried again. Still nothing. <br><br>
He started to panic, but remembered his back-up chute. So, he pulled that cord.<br>
Nothing happens. Sw frantically begins pulling both cords, but to no avail. <br><br>
Suddenly, he looks down and he can't believe his eyes. Another man,  ED is in the air with him, but Ed is going *up*! <br><br>
Just as Ed passes by, Sw, the skydiver -- by this time scared out of his wits -- yells, &quot;Hey, do you know anything about skydiving?&quot; <br><br>
Ed yelled back, &quot;No! Do you know anything about gas stoves?&quot; <br><br>

